---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import LegalArticle from '../components/LegalArticle.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Shipping & Returns"
  description="Delivery of FeatureSignals as a digital SaaS product—no physical shipping. Cancellation and subscription terms."
>
  <LegalArticle title="Shipping &amp; Returns">
    <p>
      FeatureSignals is a <strong>software-as-a-service (SaaS)</strong> and <strong>IT services</strong> offering. We deliver access to our platform electronically over the Internet.
      This page explains what that means for “shipping” and “returns” in the sense often requested by payment providers and marketplaces—mirroring how many Indian and global B2B SaaS
      companies document the same topic.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Shipping of goods</h2>
    <p>
      We <strong>do not ship physical products</strong>. There are no parcels, delivery timelines for merchandise, or freight charges. Service delivery consists of enabling your account,
      providing access to the dashboard and APIs, and maintaining the hosted environment according to our service descriptions and status communications.
    </p>

    <h2>2. When access begins</h2>
    <p>
      After you complete registration and, for paid plans, successful payment authorization, we provision access as soon as reasonably practicable—typically immediately or within a short period.
      If onboarding is delayed by verification, technical maintenance, or factors outside our control, we will use commercially reasonable efforts to restore or complete access promptly.
    </p>

    <h2>3. “Returns” for digital services</h2>
    <p>
      Because our product is intangible and consumed on an ongoing basis, <strong>returns in the retail sense do not apply</strong>. Instead:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>You may <strong>cancel your subscription</strong> to stop future renewals, as described in our <a href="/refund-policy">Refund Policy</a> and account billing settings.</li>
      <li>Eligibility for refunds for fees already charged is governed by the <a href="/refund-policy">Refund Policy</a> and applicable law.</li>
      <li>Self-hosted deployments using our open-source software are governed by the Apache-2.0 license and your own infrastructure choices—not by physical return policies.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Service availability</h2>
    <p>
      We aim for high availability but do not guarantee uninterrupted operation. Planned maintenance, security updates, or upstream provider outages may affect access. We publish status
      information when appropriate and prioritize security and data integrity.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Address and contact</h2>
    <p>
      Official correspondence for orders, billing, and support is handled electronically. Contact
      <a href="mailto:support@featuresignals.com">support@featuresignals.com</a>. Our <a href="/about">About</a> page lists our legal / operating name and business category for verification purposes.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Related policies</h2>
    <p>
      Please also read our <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a> and <a href="/refund-policy">Refund Policy</a> for how we handle personal data and payments.
    </p>
  </LegalArticle>
</Layout>
